<p>This code generates a sitemap with all the posts on your blog.</p>

<p>Save the file and push it to your blog’s repository.</p>

<p>Submit your sitemap to search engines. You can do this by adding the following line to your robots.txt file:</p>

<p>bash
Copy code
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Sitemap: http://localhost:4000/sitemap.xml</code>
This tells search engines where to find your sitemap.</p>

<p>Test your sitemap using a tool like Google’s Search Console to make sure it’s working correctly.</p>
